args: You're planning to hold an\nAlberian chess tournament?
Yeah, I thought it would be fun if the folks\nwho like games could all play together.
Hope says you're quite the board game\naficionado, but how are you at chess?
I mean, I'm good at board games\nbecause I play 'em all the time.
I've only played a little chess, but I think\nI can handle a tournament. ...Hopefully.
Anyway, if you need more bodies\nor whatever, I'll sign up.
Really? Great! Then I'll be cheering\nyou on when the big day comes.
You seem happy, Sam. Is it 'cause\nI decided to do this on my own?
Well, games are about all I'm good at,\nand I feel like they give me a chance\nto be more of a normal, social kid.
Heh. You're always in my corner,\naren't you? Thanks, buddy.
All right, I'm gonna give this my best!
Eventually, the day of the tournament came.\nEugene secured victory after victory,\nand made it to the semi-finals.
Looks like it's the end of the road\nfor me! Nice job, lad.
(Oh man, I might actually win this entire\ntourney. Games really ARE my deal!)
You're amazing, Eugene!\nI think you've got this in the bag!
Thanks, guys. I'll do my best!
Think I'll cheer on that Eugene fellow, too.
I wasn't expecting you to lose, Aurien.
His offense was spectacular. I could feel\nhis passion in every move, as if this was\nhis favorite place in the world.
I probably could have distracted him\nwith some clever words, but that\nseemed a touch unfair.
Thanks for taking the honorable path.
No thanks required—I'm all about staking\nthe future on the promise of youth!
But his next opponent won't be so easy;\nI fear he's in for a significant challenge.
Yeah, I know. He's going to be facing...
I-I'll move my stone trebuchet forward!
Then I will use the provided opening\nto capture your sorcerer princess.
No! That was the crux of my offense!
(Who IS this guy? He's a monster!)
(I've played a perfect game so far\nand he's STILL walloping me!)
(No, I can't give up. Not now.\nThere has to be a way out of this!)
If you spend all of your time trying to\nturn this game around in a single move,\nvictory will ever elude you.

Victory is not something discovered by a
moment's sudden inspiration—it is a goal
attained through thorough, deliberate
thought and planning.

Do not narrow your horizons to a single
move. Instead, examine the big picture—
because a single misjudgment on whether
to attack or retreat can ruin any strategy.
(Wait, so what's he saying? Does he think\nI should play a more defensive battle?)
(OR...he's just playing mind games!\nDon't listen to him, Eugene!)
I'm moving my sellsword\ninto the enemy formation!
(This is a long shot, but if I can catch him\noff guard and break through his defense...)
So you chose to continue your assault?\nI applaud your valiant efforts.
However, my woodland archer can now\ntake advantage of the weak point this\nreckless advance made in your formation.
I lost? No! This can't be happening...
Ooof. Tough break there, Eugene.\nBut hey, you gave as good as you got!
Shut up! I don't need your pity!
Yikes! Er, sorry. I didn't mean\nto be insensitive, I promise.
W-wait, no! I didn't mean...\nUgh, that came out all wrong.
The poor lad had tears in his eyes.
Yes, he took the loss pretty hard.

Yeah, I know. But I can't do this anymore.
I only had one thing I was good at,
and that Leif guy just came in and
wiped the floor with me.
Then I yelled at Hope when he was just\ntrying to support me. I'm an IDIOT, gosh!
Nope. Not this time, buddy.\nI'm just a big dumb failure.
I can't do anything right...\nAnd I can't get along with anyone...
